## TEM Panel Reference — SQL Server Panels

### FoundationDatabasePanel

The main Foundation database panel. Fill in all fields.

| Field | Value for this host |
|-------|---------------------|
| `Host` | `server2019tc` |
| `Port` | `1433` |
| `Instance` | *(leave blank for default instance)* |
| `User` | Teamcenter DB login name |
| `Password` | Teamcenter DB login password |
| `Database Name` | Chosen Teamcenter database name |
| `Data Directory` | `C:\tcdata` |

### MSSQLSystemPanel

Shown when TEM is creating the database.

| Field | Notes |
|-------|-------|
| `Database System User` | `sa` or your DBA account |
| `Database System Password` | Available at runtime — do not embed in notes |
| `Database Directory on Database Server` | SQL data folder — must already exist |
| `Database Collation` | Default shown by TEM help: `Latin1_General_BIN` |

### MssqlPortInstancePanel

| Choice | Value |
|--------|-------|
| Connection method | `Port` (not named instance) |
| Port | `1433` |

### Configuration Categories (Reference)

These appear in the saved `configuration.xml` after install:

- `SmMssqlEngine` — Server Manager database settings (host, DB name, port, create flags)
- `TcMssqlEngine` — Teamcenter database settings (host, DB name, port, user, populate flags, UTF-8 flag)
